Common Format Specifiers:
%d - Integer
%f - Float
%lf - Double
%s - String
%c - Character



ğŸ“¤ Formatted Output
ğŸ”¸ printf()

ğŸ‘‰Outputs formatted data to the console.
ğŸ‘‰Uses format specifiers to display values in a specific way.

Example:
int age = 25;
printf("Age: %d", age); // Displays: Age: 25

Common Format Specifiers:
%d - Integer
%f - Float
%lf - Double
%s - String
%c - Character
%x - Hexadecimal

